5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING PURPOSES FOR WHICH PUBLIC USE EASEMENTS
6 MAY BE GRANTED ON STATE LAND; AMENDING SECTIONS 77-2-101, 77-2-102, AND 77-2-105, MCA;
7 AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 77-2-101, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "77-2-101. Easements for specific uses. (1) Upon proper application as provided in 77-2-102(1)
13 through (5), the board may grant easements on state lands for the following purposes:
14 (1) public uses described in 70-30-102;
15 (a)(2) schoolhouse sites and grounds;
16 (b)(3) public parks;
17 (4) public trails;
18 (c)(5) community buildings;
19 (d)(6) cemeteries;
20 (e)(7) conservation purposes:
21 (i)(a) to the department of fish, wildlife, and parks for parcels that are surrounded by or adjacent to
22 land owned by the department of fish, wildlife, and parks as of January 1, 2001; and
23 (ii)(b) to a nonprofit corporation for parcels that are surrounded by or adjacent to land owned by that
24 same nonprofit corporation as of January 1, 2001; and
25 (iii) to a nonprofit corporation for the Owen Sowerwine natural area located within section 16,
26 township 28 north, range 21 west, in Flathead County; and
27 (f) for other public uses.
28 (2) The board may grant easements on state lands for the following purposes:
