9 Section 2. Section 77-2-102, MCA, is amended to read:
10 "77-2-102. Application for easement -- survey exemptions. (1) Application for an easement on
11 state land must be made to the department. Except as provided in subsections (3) through (5), the application
12 must describe the proposed right-of-way according to survey, show the necessity for the proposed highway or
13 street or other easement, and give any additional information that the department requires.
14 (2) This application must be accompanied by two exact copies of the official plat of the proposed
15 highway, street, or other easement, verified by the affidavit of the engineer or surveyor who prepared the
16 application. These plats must show the quantity of land taken by the proposed highway or street or other
17 easement for each 40-acre tract or government lot of state land over or through which it passes and also the
18 amount of land remaining in each portion of that 40-acre tract or government lot. When considered necessary
19 by the department, these plats must show all these facts for smaller subdivisions as the circumstances may
20 render desirable for the state.
21 (3) The application must include the affidavit of a licensed engineer or professional surveyor
22 stating that the methodology used is known to be accurate to within 5 meters. The survey must be tied to an
23 established section corner or 1/4 corner monument. The department may request greater accuracy if the
24 department determines that the information is needed to adequately describe the easement.
25 (4) If the purpose of the right-of-way applied for is the transmission or distribution of electrical
26 energy or the construction and operation of pipelines or telephone, telegraph, or radio systems, the plats and
27 measurements need not be given. An exact geographical survey is not required, but the application must
28 include the description of the location of the center line of the right-of-way that refers to an established
