1 monument within a filed corner recordation form, certificate of survey, or subdivision plat. The accuracy
2 requirements of subsection (3) must be met. The entire right-of-way may be applied for in one application with
3 only one plat of the entire right-of-way required. An archaeological survey is not required if, in the opinion of the
4 department, heritage property would not be impacted.
5 (5) (a) If the purpose of the right-of-way applied for is a regional water authority provided for in Title
6 75, chapter 6, part 3, the plats and measurements need not be given. An exact geographical survey is not
7 required, but the application must include the description of the location of the center line of the right-of-way.
8 (b) The application provided for in subsection (5)(a) must be accompanied by electronic global
9 positioning system data in the Montana coordinate system, the easement location depicted on a topographical
10 map to a scale of 1:24,000, easement coordinates, and the quantity of land taken in each quarter-quarter
11 section.
12 (6) (a) The department may waive survey requirements for rights-of-way or easements provided
13 for in 77-2-101(2)(d) 77-2-101(11) when there is sufficient information to define the boundaries of the right-of-
14 way or easement to record the right-of-way or easement.
15 (b) An application for a private access road to private property must include:
16 (i) a description of appurtenant private lands historically accessed by the access road;
17 (ii) aerial photographs or images by an agency of the United States government dated prior to
18 October 1, 1997, that depict the access road; and
19 (iii) easement location depicted on a topographical map to a scale of 1:24,000.
20 (c) An application for an existing county road must include:
21 (i) documentation establishing the road pursuant to Title 7, chapter 14, part 26;
22 (ii) aerial photographs or images by an agency of the United States government dated prior to
23 October 1, 1997, that depict the county road; and
24 (iii) easement location depicted on a topographical map to a scale of 1:24,000.
25 (d) An application for an existing public utility infrastructure must include:
26 (i) evidence of installation prior to October 1, 1997, through submission of plant staking sheets,
27 photographic evidence of dated infrastructure tags, or similar evidence; and
28 (ii) easement location depicted on a topographical map to a scale of 1:24,000."
